# Draft:List of Battle for Dream Island characters__disambig_1

Battle for Dream Island is an animated web series created by twin brothers Cary and Michael Huang on January 1, 2010. The first season, Battle for Dream Island. follows 20 anthropomorphic objects (later 21). A second season, Battle for Dream Island Again, follows 11 returning contestants with 10 new ones. A fourth season, Battle for B.F.D.I., follows 64 contestants. During BFB, the season splits into Battle for B.F.B. and The Power of Two, with only 14 contestants remaining for BFB's continuation. The fifth season, The Power of Two, follows the 40 contestants from Battle for B.F.B. with the addition of two newcomers to join the season, making the total number of contestants 42.

Characters
Hosts
* Announcer is the host of the first season of Battle for Dream Island, who secretly hosted the first five episodes of Battle for Dream Island Again before making his return as the main antagonist in Battle for B.F.B. He is a gray rectangular speaker box from outer space, who offered the contestants Dream Island and frequently gets concerned over budget cuts, which often effects on who he runs the show.
* Four is the host of the fourth season of Battle for Dream Island: Battle for B.F.D.I. They are a blue integer representing the number four called an "Algebralien". They are a chaotic and mischievous often torturing contestants for fun and when provoked in the first half of BFB also not tolerating criticism. In the second half he becomes more calm, friendly and humble. They are shown to have god-like powers which he can warp reality, teleport and eliminate contestants in a pocket dimension he made in his body called the "E.X.I.T." He also frequently screeches at contestants and shoots beams at them when provoked.
* X is the co-host of the fourth season of Battle for Dream Island: Battle for B.F.D.I.
* Two is the host for the fifth season, titled Battle for Dream Island, the Power of Two.
Contestants
Debuted in Battle for Dream Island
* Blocky is a contestant on BFDI, and BFB. He is a wooden red block who likes to pull pranks on other characters. In each of the ''Blocky's Funny Doings International'' segments, he demonstrates how a contestant's recovery center can be booby-trapped so that they die repeatedly.
* Bubble is a contestant on BFDI, and BFB. She is a kindhearted and happy soap bubble that gets popped a lot. But, in later seasons she has become more anxious and sensitive.
* Coiny is a contestant on BFDI, BFDIA, BFB and TPOT. He is a nice and rude penny that has a rivalry with Firey, with whom he shares a mutual history of slapping each other. In later seasons he becomes more nicer and more thoughtful to people.
* David is a contestant on "BFDI" and "BFB". He is a mysterious poorly-drawn stick-figure who only says "Aw, Seriously?" being his catchphrase and only phrase he can say. He can also be quite antisocial, often refusing to follow directions of others.
* Eraser is a contestant on BFDI, BFB and TPOT. He is a grumpy, bored and impatient pink eraser, who has a close friendship with Pen and Blocky.
* Firey is a contestant on BFDI, BFDIA, and BFB. He is a competitive, loyal and gullible flame, who has a rivalry with Coiny having a history of slapping each other.
* Flower is a contestant on BFDI, and BFB. She is a Zeltnera venusta flowering plant. She started off in BFDI as a mean, nasty and short-tempered person who is disliked by all of the other contestants. In BFB, she becomes more friendly and upbeat.
* Golf Ball is a contestant on BFDI, BFDIA, BFB and TPOT. She is an intelligent, bossy golf ball with dimples. She has a good friendship with Tennis Ball, and she always tries to make herself as a leader.
* Ice Cube is a contestant on BFDI, BFDIA, BFB and TPOT. She is a quiet and vengeful ice cube always seeking revenge for people who disrespected her.
* Leafy is a contestant on BFDI and BFB. She is a kind-hearted, generous, impulsive, green leaf, who tries to be a people-pleaser.
* Match is a contestant on BFDI, BFDIA, and BFB. She has a close friendship will Pencil. She is friendly to some contestants and will be mean and exclude some others usually following and agreeing whatever Pencil wants to do.
* Needle is a contestant on BFDI, BFDIA, BFB and TPOT. She is a assertive, resourceful and vengeful gray sewing needle. Where she will become angry and slap any contestant that calls her "Needy".
* Pen is a contestant on BFDI, BFB and TPOT. He is a kind, loyal, empathetic and considerate white and blue ballpoint pen. He is good friends with contestants Blocky and Eraser, but he shows to be the kindest out of the three.
* Pencil is a contestant on BFDI, BFDIA, BFB and TPOT. She is caring to her friends and often sticks up for them if anyone is mean to them. She becomes a controlling and manipulative figure in BFB. In TPOT, she becomes more mentally unstable due to the events she faced in the E.X.I.T.
* Pin is a contestant on BFDI, BFDIA, BFB and TPOT. She is a confident and fierce red thumbtack who bosses people around in an attempt to become a heroic team leader. In later seasons, she displays more self-righteousness and integrity.
* Rocky is a contestant on BFDI, BFDIA, BFB and TPOT. He is a bizarre and erratic rock who barely can speak and only produces and throws up vomit.
* Snowball is a contestant on BFDI, BFDIA, BFB and TPOT. He is a competitive, jock-like, egoistical snowball who tries to act tough around people and regards anyone he does not like as weaklings.
* Spongy is a contestant on BFDI, BFDIA, and BFB. He is a gentle and sensitive fat yellow kitchen sponge who is not well-received among many contestants, with most of them considering him dead-weight for challenges.
* Teardrop is a contestant on BFDI, BFDIA, BFB and TPOT. She is a silent, rebellious and deadly blue teardrop.
* Tennis Ball is a contestant on BFDI, BFDIA, BFB, and TPOT. He is a clumsy and intelligent tennis ball who is very close friends with Golf Ball.
* Woody is a contestant on BFDI, BFDIA, and BFB. He is a piece of balsa wood who often gets nervous over things. He has panophobia.
Debuted in Battle for Dream Island Again
* Bomby is a contestant on BFDIA, BFB and TPOT. He is a jumpy and easily scared bomb who explodes often when his fuse is lit. He constantly snacks on bananas.
* Book is a contestant on BFDIA, BFB and TPOT. She is a determined, loyal and gullible green and blue hardcover book. She has a hard time controlling herself when angered, as shown in BFB, in which she marked another contestant, Taco, as a traitor.
* Donut is a contestant on BFDIA, BFB and TPOT. He is a considerate, thoughtful and arrogant jelly-filled donut who displays his rational side when he shows care for his teammates and acts as a team leader. He hosted BFB episodes 6 through 9.
* Dora is a contestant on BFDIA, and BFB. She is a calm, collected and mysterious stick figure. She is obsessed with eating islands, which is all she talks about. Like David, she also speaks a few words being "DaDaDa".
* Fries is a contestant on BFDIA, BFB and TPOT. He is a grumpy, sarcastic, serious and antipathetic cardboard cup of French fries. Fries believes that people who take the mantle of leadership are valuable.
* Gelatin is a contestant on BFDIA, and BFB. He is a laid-back, childish and immature carved of lime-flavored gelatin, who runs a steakhouse called Gelatin's Steakhouse.
* Nickel is a contestant on BFDIA, BFB and TPOT. He is a goofy, happy-go-lucky American nickel who shouts random erratic and nonsensical phrases.
* Puffball is a contestant on BFDIA, BFB and TPOT. She is a calm, bubbly, fuzzy pink ball who has a vocoded voice and fur that changes color when she talks. She has the ability to fly and float, and she is usually calm except when she is wronged.
* Ruby is a contestant on BFDIA, and BFB. She is a bubbly, silly and curious diamond-cut ruby. She enjoys playing around with other contestants and is shown to look up to contestants with leadership roles.
* Yellow Face is a contestant on BFDIA, BFB, and TPOT. He is a loud and erratic poorly-drawn yellow cartoon head that appears in mock commercial segments where he sells outlandish products. He is shown to largely hate contestants that oppose his ads or products. He runs a company called Yellow Face Inc.

Other recurring characters
* One is a blue-colored Arabic numeral. The first canonical appearance of One shows her as a lonely, self-conscious person who constantly seeks to interact with others but is dismissed or ignored. One's own mental health is shown to be deteriorating from the lack of communication with anyone, which causes her to become more aggressive around people. When she is locked inside the Moon, she turns more psychologically unstable and starts a revenge plot against the Algebraliens to repair Three.
